    "privileged_info_summary": "The task involves researching 5 chemicals on the CAMEO Chemicals website (https://cameochemicals.noaa.gov/), a real NOAA resource. Data is NOT synthetic. Verified chemical data: Allyl Alcohol (UN 1098, Class 6.1), Phosphorus Oxychloride (UN 1810), Potassium Permanganate (UN 1490, Class 5.1, reactive group 'Oxidizing Agents, Strong'), Triethylamine (UN 1296, Class 3), and Divinylbenzene (UN 1993, Class 3, reactive group 'Hydrocarbons, Aromatic'). Key discrepancies: Phosphorus Oxychloride's DOT class is primarily 6.1 (not 8 as metadata claims), its reactive group is 'Acyl Halides, Sulfonyl Halides, and Chloroformates' (not 'Acids, Strong Non-oxidizing'). Allyl Alcohol's reactive group is 'Alcohols and Polyols' (not 'Alcohols and Glycols'). Triethylamine's reactive group is 'Amines, Phosphines, and Pyridines' (not 'Amines, Aliphatic and Aromatic').",
